summary: Okay so, we all know that Lysandre is the most obvious plot twist villain ever, but I just thought of one twist that would be...
question: Okay so, we all know that Lysandre is the most obvious plot twist villain ever, but I just thought of one twist that would be better AND explain why Sycamore isn't bothered by Lysandre's... "Worrying" speeches: What if Professor Sycamore had secretly been the leader of Team Flare, with Lysandre simply being the "Face" of Team Flare? I'm not suggesting this is what was happening in canon, but imagine if that had been the case.
answer: oh, the drama of it all……personally I love villain reveals, even if they’re really obvious. So what more if they’re actually surprising? I think I’d enjoy the Sycamore idea

summary: Harry Potter characters as Pokemon trainers; Head of Houses edition
title: Harry Potter characters as Pokemon trainers; Head of Houses edition
body:
Dumbledore - Never actually got a starter Pokemon. Instead, befriended a shiny Abra, that he evolved into an Alakazam and found its mega-stone. Also has a Ho-oh named Fawkes. Runs Hogwarts School of Pokemon.

McGonagall - Starter was a Meowth that is now a Persian. Teacher of move creation, combinations, and tactics.

Snape - Starter was a Zubat that eventually became a Crobat. Teaches status condition, berries, and cure crafting.

Sprout - Oddish that is now Bellossom. Teaches basic Pokemon care.

Flitwick -  Mr. Mime was his starter. Teaches item and Pokeball crafting.

summary: Pokemon Card of the Day #1527: Cheren (Emerging Powers)
title: Pokemon Card of the Day #1527: Cheren (Emerging Powers)
body: Cheren was another choice for a drawing Supporter, and it was probably the most simple of them all. You simply drew 3 cards no matter when you played it. Its impact was lower overall than most of its competition, which meant that it rarely saw use, but it was also a card that provided some help for a deck no matter what your hand was like. There was some value in this, so while cards such as Professor Oak’s New Theory, Professor Juniper/Professor Sycamore, N, Colress, Bianca, and even Shauna saw more use overall depending on the format (which extended for 4 years into BCR-On due to reprints), Cheren was still worth a look due to its consistent nature that didn’t make you lose access to any of your cards and worked even with a bigger hand.
